\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Illustration of the metabolic transformation pipeline. Panel 1: Gaussian FIR kernels with different temporal spreads $\sigma $ demonstrate how water ($\sigma _w = 30$ hr) is absorbed more rapidly than fertilizer ($\sigma _f = 300$ hr). Panel 4: EMA filters with different memory parameters $\beta $ show how cumulative divergence tracking responds to sustained anomalies, with larger $\beta $ providing longer memory of past stress events.}}{29}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:metabolism-transformations}{{1}{29}{Illustration of the metabolic transformation pipeline. Panel 1: Gaussian FIR kernels with different temporal spreads $\sigma $ demonstrate how water ($\sigma _w = 30$ hr) is absorbed more rapidly than fertilizer ($\sigma _f = 300$ hr). Panel 4: EMA filters with different memory parameters $\beta $ show how cumulative divergence tracking responds to sustained anomalies, with larger $\beta $ providing longer memory of past stress events}{figure.1}{}}
